firefox.notes: Firefox 1 supported an invalid syntax where the character encoding is not between single or double quotes.

ie.notes: From Internet Explorer 5.5 to IE 7 (inclusive), Internet Explorer supported an invalid syntax where the character encoding is not between single or double quotes.

firefox.notes: Starting with Firefox 41, <a> without href attribute is no longer classified as interactive content: clicking it inside <label> will activate labelled content (bug 1167816).

firefox.notes: You can no longer nest an <a> element inside a <map> element to create a hotspot region — coords and shape attribute support removed.
